        "text": "What is a zero-tick pulse?"
      }
    ],
    "type": "h1"
  },
  {
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "A zero-tick, or 0-tick pulse, is any redstone pulse whose length is less than one gametick. At first, this may not seem possible, as you would think that the shortest redstone pulse would be one that turns on in gametick ~0 and turns off in the next tick, gametick ~1. Upon closer inspection of the code, we realized that a pulse could turn on in one moment in the tick and turn off in another, later moment in the tick. (see "
      },
      {
        "type": "a",
        "url": "https://technicalmc.xyz/render-post/15",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": ""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": ""
      },
      {
        "type": "a",
        "url": "https://technicalmc.xyz/render-post/15",
        "children": [
          {
            "text": "this post"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " for an explanation of tick phases)"
      }
    ],
    "type": "paragraph"
